1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,540
She only needed one interview.

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:04,480
Jago Quint was the billionaire no one could reach,

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:06,600
and that story could save her career.

4
00:00:07,060 --> 00:00:09,760
So she accepted the most dangerous deal of her life,

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,200
pretending to be his girlfriend for one night.

6
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:13,880
It was supposed to be simple.

7
00:00:14,380 --> 00:00:17,820
Walk into the ball, convince his family, and walk out with the answers she needed.

8
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,280
But when Jago's mother demanded proof of love in front of everyone,

9
00:00:21,820 --> 00:00:23,580
she did exactly what she shouldn't have.

10
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:24,780
She kissed Jago.

11
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:28,060
And that kiss, which was only supposed to be a lie,

12
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:30,260
started to feel far too real.

13
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:33,580
The newsroom smelled of reheated coffee and old paper,

14
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:37,080
and  Roenah  Pike  had  already  drunk  three  cups  before  nine

15
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:37,720
in  the  morning.

16
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:41,320
The gray light coming through the window gave every face

17
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:42,940
there the same shade of exhaustion.

18
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:46,300
The kind of fatigue that doesn't come from one bad night's sleep.

19
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:49,540
But from months, piled one on top of another.

20
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,940
She knew, hers was no different.

21
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:54,140
She held her folder against her chest,

22
00:00:54,540 --> 00:00:56,660
and crossed the narrow aisle between the desks,

23
00:00:56,660 --> 00:00:59,640
greeting with a Kurt Nord anyone who looked up.

24
00:00:59,980 --> 00:01:03,000
Wallace Vaughn was waiting for her with his elbows planted on the desk,

25
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:05,200
glasses pushed to the tip of his nose.

26
00:01:05,740 --> 00:01:08,140
The editor had a peculiar way of looking at people,

27
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:11,200
as if he were checking whether they were worth their own salary.

28
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:14,960
Roenah shut the door behind her, ignored the chair he didn't offer,

29
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:17,300
and sat down without waiting for an invitation.

30
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:19,200
I need the interview Pike.

31
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:21,440
Wallace didn't waste time on introductions,

32
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:23,880
and I need something else too.

33
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:26,940
If you're about to tell me you need a photo of Quint without his jacket,

34
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:29,180
I'm walking out of this room right now.

35
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:30,340
I need a file.

36
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,740
The sentence landed in the middle of the desk,

37
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:34,960
like something too heavy for the furniture.

38
00:01:35,540 --> 00:01:40,480
Roenah raised an eyebrow, waiting for him to refraise to apologise to turn it into a joke.

39
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,240
Wallace did none of that.

40
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:45,440
He simply laced his fingers and kept looking at her,

41
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:47,520
as if he were collecting on an old debt.

42
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,120
Proof, he added,

43
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:52,160
that that empire is hiding something it shouldn't be hiding.

44
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:54,160
Everyone hied something Pike.

45
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,920
You just need to find out what.

46
00:01:56,400 --> 00:02:00,320
You want me to get inside the home of the most closed off family in the south.

47
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:03,460
Land the interview no one's managed to land in 10 years,

48
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:06,160
and still walk out of there with compromising material.

49
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:09,240
I'm telling you that your job here depends on it.

50
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,780
She didn't answer right away.

51
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,540
She sat staring at the coffee stain on the rim of his mug.

52
00:02:14,060 --> 00:02:17,540
Calculating how much of next month's salary was already committed to rent,

53
00:02:18,020 --> 00:02:20,100
how much was still owed on her mother's bill.

54
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:23,580
The window behind Hollis let in the muffled noise of the street.

55
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,340
A horn, a quick step.

56
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:29,880
The city running nonstop while she sat there deciding how far she was willing to go.

57
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:34,580
Then she nodded once, short, like someone signing a contract they haven't yet read.

58
00:02:35,140 --> 00:02:38,240
Marlo Trent intercepted her in the hallway with two fresh coffees,

59
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,360
and a smile that was already a question.

60
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:43,980
Marlo was a copy editor, a colleague of three years,

61
00:02:44,420 --> 00:02:48,000
and the only person in the newsroom who understood when Roenah needed silence

62
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,520
and when she needed noise.

63
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:53,480
You look like someone who just sold her soul, Marlo remarked,

64
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:54,660
handing over the hot-a-cup.

65
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:55,820
Was it for much?

66
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,740
It was for next month's rent.

67
00:02:58,340 --> 00:03:02,100
Marlo laughed, a short laugh, cut off halfway by the awareness

68
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:05,620
that the joke was worth more to herself than to Roenah.

69
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:09,020
She leaned her shoulder against Roenahs as they walked down the hallway,

70
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:13,200
and for a moment, Roenah felt like dropping everything right there,

71
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:16,100
walking out the front door, and never coming back.

72
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,040
She didn't.

73
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:19,600
She drank the coffee until it burned her tongue.

74
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:23,700
Afternoon came quickly, and with it a note left at the front desk.

75
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:27,160
No sender, just her name on the front of the envelope,

76
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:30,220
written in black pen and handwriting that wasn't a friend,

77
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:34,700
slanted controlled letters, each one in its exact place.

78
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:38,160
Roenah turned the envelope over twice before opening it,

79
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:40,440
inside just an address and a time.

80
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,480
Nothing more.

81
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:44,260
The office it pointed to was three blocks away,

82
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:46,540
in a discreet building she had never noticed,

83
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:49,280
despite having walked past it hundreds of times.

84
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,740
The sign at the entrance simply read Ashford and Associates,

85
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:54,740
in letters too small to draw attention.

86
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:57,100
Roenah climbed the steps with her folder,

87
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,600
still pressed against her chest,

88
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:01,520
and greeted the receptionist with the name that was on the note.

89
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,300
The man who received her was younger than she expected.

90
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,480
Tall, navy, suit, no tie,

91
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,320
with that kind of discretion only old money teachers.

92
00:04:09,860 --> 00:04:12,960
He extended his hand and introduced himself as Silas Ashford,

93
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:17,180
the Quint family's lawyer, a friend of Jago's since their boarding school days.

94
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:19,480
The information came without fanfare,

95
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,820
the way someone hands over a business card.

96
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,260
Have a seat, Miss Pike.

97
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:26,340
His voice had the same tone as the handwriting on the envelope.

98
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,860
I'll be brief because the proposal is brief.

99
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:29,920
I'm curious.

100
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:34,320
Mr. Quint agrees to grant a two-hour interview to your publication.

101
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:38,020
No restrictions on subject matter, except one.

102
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:39,960
Silas made a minimal pause.

103
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:43,040
The kind of pause lawyers used to let the client swallow

104
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,380
the next piece of information.

105
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:48,500
In return, you would attend the family's Gallaboll in Savannah

106
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,020
as his companion on Friday.

107
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:52,320
One night, just one.

108
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:55,660
Roenah laughed before her brain authorized her mouth.

109
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:56,940
Companion.

110
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,740
That's the word he preferred.

111
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,920
And what word didn't he prefer?

112
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:03,960
The corner of Silas's mouth moved half a millimeter,

113
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:07,200
almost the beginning of a smile but nothing followed through.

114
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,520
He slid a black envelope across the desk,

115
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,920
sealed with her name written on the front

116
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,780
in the same slanted, controlled handwriting as the first note.

117
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:18,080
Letters she now recognized without effort,

118
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:20,940
and which definitely did not belong to Silas.

119
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,560
The rules are in there.

120
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:23,800
One read is enough.

121
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,540
He expects an answer today.

122
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:28,260
Roenah looked at the black envelope for too long.

123
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:29,800
She thought about the rent.

124
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,420
She thought about the look on Holasis face.

125
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,480
She thought about the old photograph of the reclusive billionaire

126
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:38,440
that had circulated through the papers forever.

127
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:41,120
Always the same profile of a clenched jaw.

128
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:44,600
Always the same gaze that didn't invite anyone to stay.

129
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:48,040
She tucked the envelope into her folder without opening it.

130
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:49,940
Tell him I'll be in Savannah on Friday.

131
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:53,740
Silas nodded like someone who already knew the answer before the question.

132
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:58,040
He rose, shook her hand again, and walked her to the door with

133
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,020
practiced courtesy.

134
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:02,260
Before closing the handle he said almost without voice,

135
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,500
he's not what the press writes that's all.

136
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,320
Roenah didn't ask what he meant.

137
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:08,100
She preferred not to know yet.

138
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:11,960
Marlo was waiting for her on the street with a cigarette that pretended to be lit.

139
00:06:12,420 --> 00:06:15,540
The kind of theatre she used as an excuse to loiter on corners.

140
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:18,440
Roenah handed over the black envelope without ceremony.

141
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,240
A friend turned the object over in her hand,

142
00:06:21,660 --> 00:06:23,700
studied the seal with more attention than necessary,

143
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,080
and gave it back.

144
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:27,140
Don't open it now, Marlo said,

145
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,380
open it on the train, it's prettier that way.

146
00:06:29,820 --> 00:06:30,240
Pretty ya.

147
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:33,060
Do you want to be someone else's story or make history?

148
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:36,440
If it's the second, you open it on the train alone,

149
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:39,320
and you cry if you need to cry without anyone seeing.

150
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,960
It's the least you deserve.

151
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:44,220
Roenah laughed and the laugh pulled some of the weight off her back.

152
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:47,380
She rested her forehead on Marlo's shoulder for a short second.

153
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:50,940
Just enough to remember she still had a friend in that grey city,

154
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,680
and then she went home to pack.

155
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:55,280
The station was too crowded for her taste.

156
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,120
Roenah dragged her luggage between hurried bodies,

157
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:00,500
bought a sandwich she wasn't going to eat,

158
00:07:00,780 --> 00:07:02,480
and settled by the window of the car.

159
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:05,800
The seats smelled of dust and warm synthetic leather.

160
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:09,680
That smell of a place where many people have passed without leaving a trace.

161
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:12,160
She sat staring at the tracks for a while,

162
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:15,480
before taking the black envelope out of the inner pocket of her bag.

163
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,920
The seal gave way with a dry sound.

164
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,560
Inside, three folded sheets.

165
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:24,580
The first two carried instructions written with almost legal precision.

166
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:27,080
Times, names she should memorize,

167
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,560
clothes that would be delivered to the hotel.

168
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:32,940
What to say if anyone asked how long they had known each other?

169
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:36,460
Roenah read them with the same attention she gave to story contracts,

170
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,440
mentally noting every detail,

171
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,320
every gap between the lines.

172
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:45,760
The third sheet was smaller, a single line written by hand, unsigned.

173
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,480
Don't smile at anyone like you believe it.

174
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,920
Only smile when I'm looking.

175
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:51,520
She read it three times.

176
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:52,940
She put it away again.

177
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:57,460
She looked out the window as the train picked up speed and the city opened into suburb,

178
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:58,440
then countryside,

179
00:07:59,140 --> 00:07:59,620
then nothing.

180
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:04,300
And she couldn't decide whether that was an order, a warning, or a request.

181
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:07,040
The train arrived in Savannah in the late afternoon.

182
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:10,300
The air changed before she even stepped onto the platform.

183
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:12,340
Warmer, denser,

184
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:15,280
laid in with a sweet perfume she couldn't yet name.

185
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:16,800
Magnolia maybe.

186
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:18,820
Or something that grew near water.

187
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:21,940
Roenah crossed the station with her folder under her arm,

188
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:25,340
looking for the driver who would be waiting with her name on a sign.

189
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:30,620
She found the dark car outside, a man in a suit opening the back door without ceremony.

190
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:35,980
Before getting in, she looked one last time at the city's skyline and saw in the distance,

191
00:08:36,540 --> 00:08:40,960
the high roof of the quint mansion cut against the sky that was beginning to turn orange.

192
00:08:41,420 --> 00:08:43,020
Too big, too old,

193
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,500
the kind of house that doesn't invite you in.

194
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:46,880
It absorbs you.

195
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,700
Roenah sat on the leather seat,

196
00:08:49,140 --> 00:08:51,040
rested her head against the cold glass,

197
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,680
and pressed the black envelope against her lap,

198
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:56,760
like someone clutching a boarding pass to another country.

199
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,140
She took the sheet out one more time.

200
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,180
Only smile when I'm looking.

201
00:09:01,620 --> 00:09:04,140
She re-read it, folded it, put it away.

202
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:05,740
The car started up,

203
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:09,900
and the streets of Savannah began to pass by outside like a borrowed set,

204
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:14,760
with the moss heavy trees and the old houses that each guarded their own version of a secret.

205
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:17,880
And for the first time since Holly's Vaughn had added the word,

206
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,900
file, Roenah Pike wondered,

207
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:23,580
whether she could go home as the same person who had boarded the train.

208
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:26,460
The hotel suite was bigger than her entire apartment,

209
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:30,080
with a soft smell of jasmine that seemed built into the walls.

210
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:33,580
Roenah looked at herself in the oval mirror for a long time,

211
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:37,500
adjusting the wine-colored silk dress they had left hanging behind the door.

212
00:09:37,860 --> 00:09:39,400
The fabric fell effortlessly.

213
00:09:39,940 --> 00:09:43,780
The kind of piece that only existed when someone paid for it without thinking twice.

214
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:47,420
The driver knocked at the door at the exact time indicated in the envelope.

215
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:51,920
Roenah went down, crossed the lobby under stairs she pretended not to notice,

216
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,080
and found the car waiting at the curb.

217
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,780
The back door opened before she touched the handle,

218
00:09:57,220 --> 00:10:00,820
and the first thing she saw inside was the impeccable crease of dark trousers,

219
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:03,740
running down to a pair of polished black shoes.

220
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,740
Jago Quint was seated on the other side of the seat,

221
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:11,000
with one knee slightly apart from the other, hands resting on his own thighs.

222
00:10:11,540 --> 00:10:13,860
He didn't stand, didn't extend his hand.

223
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:17,840
He merely tilted his chin and inch toward the empty spot beside him,

224
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:18,500
and waited.

225
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:22,180
Roenah got in, adjusted her skirt with a quick gesture,

226
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:24,920
and shut the door with more force than necessary.

227
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:25,980
He noticed.

228
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,640
She saw that he noticed.

229
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:29,280
Neither of them commented.

230
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:30,860
Good evening, Miss Pike.

231
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:34,720
His voice was lower than she had imagined from any interview she'd ever read.

232
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,880
A voice that didn't rise because it didn't need to.

233
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:41,240
Roenah turned her face and looked at him full on for the first time,

234
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:45,380
and had the displeasure of confirming that the portraits published over the years did

235
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:46,220
him no justice.

236
00:10:46,740 --> 00:10:51,940
In person, he was a sculpture of a straight jaw, dark hair combed back with calculated

237
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:57,320
carelessness, and eyes that decided the temperature of the room before saying anything at all.

238
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,780
Good evening, Mr. Quint.

239
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:00,260
Jago will do.

240
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,720
Then Roenah will do.

241
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,660
He nodded almost imperceptibly.

242
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:07,840
The car started up, and for a while the two of them sat in silence.

243
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:13,700
Roenah noticed his hands resting on his knees, long fingers, a silver watch with no visible

244
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:14,160
brand.

245
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:19,640
She also noticed that the seat between them held a thin leather folder, closed, with one corner

246
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,900
leaning against the glass.

247
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:21,920
Details.

248
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,620
She collected details.

249
00:11:24,260 --> 00:11:25,200
Are the rules clear?

250
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:27,000
He asked without turning his face.

251
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:27,720
Crystal.

252
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:28,780
Any questions?

253
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:29,800
One.

254
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:32,940
Roenah waited until he finally turned his gaze to her.

255
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,380
How long do you intend for this night to last?

256
00:11:35,380 --> 00:11:38,240
As long as necessary, that's not an answer.

257
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:39,760
It's the only one I have.

258
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:43,940
He looked forward again and Roenah accepted defeat in that round without arguing.

259
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:47,140
She kept watching his profile against the dark window.

260
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:52,360
The hard line of his jaw, the way his thumb pressed against his own knee in a steady rhythm,

261
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:54,980
like someone counting something inside himself.

262
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:58,200
She stored the gesture in her memory, and said nothing.

263
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:01,840
The Quint mentioned appeared at the end of the avenue of tall trees,

264
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,120
lit from outside like a theatre set.

265
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:06,840
Roenah drew a deep breath before the car stopped.

266
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:08,540
Jago got out first.

267
00:12:08,940 --> 00:12:13,200
Went around the vehicle and opened her door with a courtesy that sounded more rehearsed than

268
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:13,680
sincere.

269
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,280
He offered his arm.

270
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:16,220
She accepted.

271
00:12:16,780 --> 00:12:20,560
His palm brushed briefly against her hand as he helped her position herself,

272
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:22,260
and the temperature changed.

273
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:24,920
Don't smile at anyone like you believe it.

274
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:25,560
He murmured.

275
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:28,640
Barely moving his lips as they climbed the steps.

276
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,580
You already warned me in writing.

277
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:32,280
I'm reinforcing it.

278
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:34,980
The main hall swallowed them the moment the door opened.

279
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,440
Roenah smelled it before she saw anything.

280
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:39,500
Magnolia and old money.

281
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:42,780
Exactly as Silas had said in the instruction note.

282
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,180
The white walls rose high to a ceiling of worked stucco,

283
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:50,640
and everywhere there were antique chandeliers spreading a honey-colored light over the guests.

284
00:12:51,260 --> 00:12:55,380
Long dresses, emerald chocas, men in black tuxedoes,

285
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:57,120
greeting each other without enthusiasm.

286
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:00,300
Jago introduced her to three couples in a row,

287
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:02,520
always with the same assembled sentence.

288
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,680
My companion for the evening, Roenah Pike.

289
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,640
No complicated surnames.

290
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:08,780
No deer.

291
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:09,900
No love.

292
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,260
Roenah smiled in just the right measure,

293
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,880
answered questions in just the right measure,

294
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,340
and noticed everything.

295
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,800
She noticed that he avoided the terrace.

296
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:22,640
Twice a waiter passed offering to take guests out of the outdoor area.

297
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,520
And both times Jago declined,

298
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:26,760
with a minimal gesture of his chin,

299
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,880
without even looking at the glass door.

300
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:32,180
She also noticed that his gaze had one point,

301
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:34,400
tripped over an empty chair near the window.

302
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:36,840
A chair upholstered in dark green velvet,

303
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:39,240
slightly set apart from the rest of the arrangement,

304
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:43,080
as if it belonged to someone who used to sit there and hadn't arrived yet.

305
00:13:43,380 --> 00:13:44,320
He looked away quickly.

306
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:45,900
Roenah stored it.

307
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:47,340
What an unlikely evening.

308
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,860
The voice came from behind her sweetest syrup heated too much.

309
00:13:51,380 --> 00:13:54,640
Roenah turned and found a woman with red hair pinned in a low bun,

310
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:58,560
an emerald green dress, a smile that didn't reach her eyes.

311
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:00,960
Jago stiffened beside her.

312
00:14:01,140 --> 00:14:03,200
Odeit, he greeted her without warmth.

313
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,120
Jago.

314
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:06,960
Odeit Mashaan extended her hand to Roenah,

315
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:10,400
palm down the gesture of someone expecting reverence,

316
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:11,700
and the companion.

317
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:12,860
How interesting.

318
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,380
What do you do dear?

319
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:15,420
I write.

320
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:18,880
A. Odeit seemed to decide something in silence.

321
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,180
How brave of him to bring you here?

322
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:23,160
Brave of me to agree to come.

323
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:24,440
Odeit laughed.

324
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:27,040
A short note that contained nothing of laughter.

325
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:29,500
Then she moved off with a wave of her fingers,

326
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:32,320
leaving behind a trail of expensive perfume.

327
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,940
Jago rested his hand at the small of Roenah's back

328
00:14:35,940 --> 00:14:39,860
for just a second, a gesture of ownership that wasn't affection.

329
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:41,520
Then he withdrew it.

330
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:43,320
You didn't need to provoke her.

331
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,320
He remarked.

332
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:44,600
Low.

333
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,200
I did, actually.

334
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,480
He didn't answer.

335
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:49,720
But the corner of his mouth moved a millimeter,

336
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:53,100
and Roenah registered it as if it were the headline of the month.

337
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:54,820
It wasn't a smile yet.

338
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,080
It was close.

339
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:59,000
The silence in the hall changed texture

340
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,940
before she understood why.

341
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,800
It was as if the air had drawn back a few inches,

342
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:08,160
and everybody there in Unison had turned their heads in the same direction.

343
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,500
Roenah followed the others gaze,

344
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:13,640
and saw Udora quint entering through the main door.

345
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:16,120
The matriarch didn't need to announce herself.

346
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:20,540
A long black dress, a pearl necklace that fell to the middle of her chest,

347
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,720
gray hair pinned with a rigidity that allowed no discussion.

348
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,140
She crossed the hall without greeting anyone,

349
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:28,580
and stopped before her son and his companion,

350
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:31,340
with the expression of someone appraising merchandise.

351
00:15:32,220 --> 00:15:33,880
Good evening, mother, said Jego.

352
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:36,060
Udora didn't answer her son.

353
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:38,100
She turned her pale eyes to Roenah,

354
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,620
and examined her from shoes to hairstyle,

355
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:42,500
with a surgical calm.

356
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,620
Then she stepped half a step closer,

357
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:48,880
and the voice that came out of her was low, but sharp enough to cut the entire hall.

358
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,160
I don't see love here, my son.

359
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:53,880
The silence closed around the three of them.

360
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,820
Roenah felt Jego's body stiffened beside her,

361
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,820
his shoulders rising half an inch.

362
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:01,560
Udora stayed put, chin raised waiting.

363
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:03,580
Proof said the matriarch.

364
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:05,800
If it's true, prove it.

365
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:09,520
The entire hall turned, heads lifted from champagne glasses,

366
00:16:10,060 --> 00:16:11,000
conversations ceased,

367
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:12,940
waiters stopped where they stood,

368
00:16:13,420 --> 00:16:17,240
Roenah felt the weight of the whole hall falling on her and Jego at the same time.

369
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:18,380
He locked up.

370
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:19,820
She saw that he locked up.

371
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:22,240
His thumb stopped counting on his own hip,

372
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,440
his jaw hardened,

373
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:26,960
and for a whole second, no decision came out of his body.

374
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,620
Roenah decided for him.

375
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:31,680
She raised her hand, took his face by the side and pulled.

376
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:35,900
His mouth met hers with a hesitation of someone who hadn't rehearsed this scene,

377
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:38,940
and for an instant, Roenah thought he wouldn't respond.

378
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:40,920
Then his breath faltered.

379
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,320
She felt the falter,

380
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:44,680
felt the air caught halfway up his chest,

381
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:49,120
felt his hand rise by reflex to her back and settle between her shoulder blades,

382
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,840
with a pressure that didn't belong to the charade.

383
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:54,300
The kiss was supposed to last a second.

384
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:55,960
It lasted three.

385
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,080
Maybe more.

386
00:16:57,580 --> 00:17:01,420
Roenah lost count somewhere between the moment he tilted his head a little to the side,

387
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:05,160
and the moment she herself forgot there was a hall around them.

388
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:08,180
When they pulled apart, she opened her eyes first.

389
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:09,980
He took half a second longer,

390
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:13,140
and what Roenah saw on his face when he finally looked back,

391
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,260
was the same thing she felt inside,

392
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,660
and which she wasn't prepared to name yet.

393
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:20,000
Udora stepped back half a step.

394
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:23,340
She adjusted her pearl necklace with a calculated carelessness,

395
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:27,780
and the corner of her mouth drew a line that wasn't a smile but pretended to be.

396
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:28,200
Good.

397
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:29,740
Mermaid the matriarch.

398
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,800
I hope to see you again many times.

399
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:32,660
Many.

400
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,000
She turned on her heels and moved off.

401
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:37,700
The hall little by little began to breathe again.

402
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,720
Conversations returned like a discreet murmur.

403
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:41,740
Waters moved.

404
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,940
Someone laughed in the distance at something that wasn't funny.

405
00:17:44,940 --> 00:17:47,040
Roenah kept looking at Jago.

406
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,840
His hand was still on her back forgotten there,

407
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,180
in no hurry to leave.

408
00:17:51,580 --> 00:17:53,240
He took his time pulling it back.

409
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:56,960
When he did, his fingers passed slowly over the silk of the dress,

410
00:17:57,100 --> 00:18:00,340
like someone memorizing a path they might need to retrace later.

411
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:03,780
Across the hall Odec-Marshon watched them with a glass in her hand,

412
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:05,980
and her smile was now a different one.

413
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:07,780
Roenah registered it.

414
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:08,560
Stored it.

415
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:09,640
She already knew,

416
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:10,920
without needing a warning,

417
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:13,040
that that woman would want payback.

418
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:15,000
Jago leaned in very slightly,

419
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:18,300
and spoke close to her ear so low that only she could hear.

420
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:19,800
You owe me an explanation.

421
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:21,220
For the kiss?

422
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:22,780
For the length of the kiss.

423
00:18:23,420 --> 00:18:24,360
Roenah didn't answer.

424
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:26,180
She didn't know the answer yet.

425
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,680
She took the glass away to her,

426
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:30,420
drank a sip she didn't even feel go down,

427
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:33,160
and looked again at the empty chair near the window.

428
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:36,600
Someone at some point had sat in it.

429
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,660
Someone who now was no longer there,

430
00:18:39,020 --> 00:18:40,200
and Roenah Pike,

431
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,640
who had collected details since childhood,

432
00:18:43,180 --> 00:18:45,620
understood that the most important story of that night,

433
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:49,440
had nothing to do with the reason Hollis Vaughan had sent her there.

434
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:51,920
The morning after the ball arrived without ceremony.

435
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:55,560
The Savannah Sun came through the gaps in the curtain of the guest room,

436
00:18:55,860 --> 00:18:58,840
at the Quint Mansion with an almost impolite insistence,

437
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:03,540
and Roenah Pike opened her eyes before she remembered exactly where she was.

438
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,900
It took a whole instant for the high ceiling,

439
00:19:06,260 --> 00:19:07,340
the carved footboard,

440
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:11,160
and the thick silence of the house to organize themselves in her head,

441
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:13,160
only then did the kiss come back.

442
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,340
It came back first through her lip,

443
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:17,220
then through the nape of her neck,

444
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:18,480
then through her stomach.

445
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:21,420
Three seconds that now carried the weight of biography.

446
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:24,560
She sat on the edge of the bed and looked at her own hands.

447
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:25,780
They were cold.

448
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:29,080
Someone had left a coffee tray on the sideboard beside the door,

449
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:30,620
during the night probably,

450
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:32,760
because the cup was no longer steaming.

451
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:37,820
Decided a short note, written by hand in a hand writing she recognized at once,

452
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,680
garden, whenever you can.

453
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,800
J. Roenah reread the note twice just to prove to herself

454
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,740
that it hadn't unsettled her.

455
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:45,660
It didn't stick.

456
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:47,880
The garden was at the back of the house,

457
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:49,280
far from the main hall.

458
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:52,200
She noticed that as a small paleide housekeeper,

459
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,180
let her down a corridor of portraits.

460
00:19:54,780 --> 00:19:57,000
The woman introduced herself as Neeve,

461
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,120
lightly squeezed Roenah's arm and said,

462
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:01,080
in an accent from rural Georgia,

463
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:03,320
that Mr. J. Roenah was already waiting.

464
00:20:03,820 --> 00:20:06,020
There was warmth in her voice but also scrutiny.

465
00:20:06,820 --> 00:20:09,640
Roenah smiled with her mouth closed and asked nothing.

466
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:13,600
J. Roenah was standing near an old rose bush with his back to the house.

467
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:16,100
White shirt sleeves folded to the elbow,

468
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:17,920
hair still wet from his shower.

469
00:20:18,460 --> 00:20:20,480
He turned when he heard the gravel and for a second,

470
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,920
just one, his eyes met hers unguarded,

471
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,480
without their usual controlled gleam.

472
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,680
Then his jaw firmed up again.

473
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:29,740
Did you sleep?

474
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,860
As much as I could, she answered,

475
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:33,420
the house makes noises.

476
00:20:33,980 --> 00:20:37,320
It does. He pointed with his chin toward a cast iron bench.

477
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:40,760
Sit with me. We need to work out what comes next.

478
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:43,980
Roenah obeyed, but chose to sit in profile,

479
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:46,960
knees turned outward. A small defense he noticed.

480
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:48,280
He said nothing.

481
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:50,620
You have the interview, J. Go began,

482
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:53,580
his voice low and chosen word by word.

483
00:20:54,060 --> 00:20:55,020
That's still standing,

484
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,740
but last night raised an issue I didn't foresee.

485
00:20:57,740 --> 00:21:00,240
My mother didn't believe it until the kiss.

486
00:21:00,740 --> 00:21:02,040
Maybe she believed it afterward.

487
00:21:02,540 --> 00:21:03,780
If you disappear tomorrow,

488
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,580
she'll get suspicious again.

489
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,400
And I'll have three candidates on the table by Sunday.

490
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:10,260
You're asking me for more days.

491
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,800
I'm asking for weeks.

492
00:21:12,420 --> 00:21:16,160
Roenah swallowed the small shock and breathed through her mouth before answering.

493
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:17,460
Weeks of what?

494
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,640
Appearances. A dinner here and event there.

495
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:24,400
Enough for Savannah to believe you're the woman who finally got into this house.

496
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:25,240
He paused.

497
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:27,200
Same payment, same interview.

498
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,760
Just a longer timeline.

499
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:30,560
There was logic in the proposal.

500
00:21:31,140 --> 00:21:32,020
And there was a trap.

501
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:33,160
She knew both.

502
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:34,360
And if I refuse.

503
00:21:34,980 --> 00:21:37,600
You get the interview anyway, he said without hesitating.

504
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,980
We agreed on something and I don't undo what's agreed.

505
00:21:41,580 --> 00:21:43,240
That was what disarmed her.

506
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,220
Not the proposal.

507
00:21:44,660 --> 00:21:46,200
The resolution of the proposal.

508
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:48,400
Roenah bit the inside of her cheek.

509
00:21:48,860 --> 00:21:51,600
Looked at the nearest rose, counted to three and said yes.

510
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:52,780
He didn't smile.

511
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:56,240
He just nodded slightly, like someone closing a clause.

512
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:58,900
But when she stood up to go back into the house,

513
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:01,440
his hand brushed her back for half a second.

514
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,520
Had a spot below her shoulder blade.

515
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,760
And lingered an instant longer than any contract required.

516
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:09,200
She stored the gesture alongside the others.

517
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:10,560
She was already collecting.

518
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:14,220
The following weeks arrived slowly and without a truce.

519
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:17,100
Roenah began to split herself between the newsroom,

520
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:20,440
where Marlo covered her shifts with increasingly irritated humour.

521
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,900
And the streets of Savannah,

522
00:22:22,540 --> 00:22:25,800
where she learned there were neighborhoods where the air smelled of wet jasmine,

523
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:28,680
and others where it only smelled of hoarded money.

524
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,800
Jago always sent for her at the station,

525
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:33,540
with the same driver and always in the same car.

526
00:22:33,940 --> 00:22:36,400
He waited for her inside, in the back seat,

527
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:38,620
shoulder leaning against the opposite door.

528
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:43,140
One Tuesday, he took her to an antique's fair under the oaks of the old square.

529
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,920
Roenah stopped in front of a tray of loose pendants

530
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:48,440
and picked up one shaped like a crooked owl.

531
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:52,060
Half green with age, set with ridiculous red stones.

532
00:22:52,060 --> 00:22:56,620
It's ugly, she said, smiling at the object as if it were an accomplice.

533
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:58,380
It is, Jago agreed.

534
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,580
She put the pendant back on the tray.

535
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:02,160
She didn't ask for it.

536
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:04,260
Didn't haggle, didn't look at it again.

537
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:07,560
Half an hour later, when they were heading back to the car,

538
00:23:07,980 --> 00:23:11,140
he passed the dark velvet box into her hand without any ceremony.

539
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,660
And Roenah stood in the middle of the sidewalk,

540
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:16,880
holding the crooked owl as if it were a live animal.

541
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,260
You didn't haggle, she remarked.

542
00:23:19,260 --> 00:23:21,860
No, he opened the car door for her.

543
00:23:22,020 --> 00:23:23,500
I knew what it was worth to you.

544
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:27,420
It was that day that Roenah didn't turn on the recorder for the entire afternoon.

545
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:32,620
She sat with Jago in his office on the 13th floor of a glass building in downtown Savannah,

546
00:23:33,140 --> 00:23:35,840
and they talked about things no interview called for.

547
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:37,700
A cousin he had and never saw.

548
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,340
A book she had read 12 times in her teens.

549
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:43,360
The specific smell of the coffee her mother used to make.

550
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:47,440
Jago poured her coffee that afternoon in a way she hadn't taught him.

551
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:51,020
Half a spoon of sugar, a splash of milk, very hot.

552
00:23:51,620 --> 00:23:55,480
Roenah looked at the cup, looked at him, and didn't ask how he knew.

553
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:59,340
Neve let the answer slip a week later in the mansions kitchen,

554
00:23:59,860 --> 00:24:04,480
while drying a crystal glass with the attention of someone handling something bigger than a glass.

555
00:24:04,980 --> 00:24:07,000
He's been sleeping better since you've been coming.

556
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:10,060
The housekeeper didn't look at Roenah as she said it.

557
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:12,660
It's not a compliment, it's an observation.

558
00:24:13,420 --> 00:24:16,220
Roenah laughed softly without breath to answer.

559
00:24:16,220 --> 00:24:18,420
Do you want to know something miss?

560
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:20,920
Neve continued, putting the glass away.

561
00:24:21,340 --> 00:24:24,280
It's been a long time since anyone asked him how his day was.

562
00:24:24,620 --> 00:24:27,800
He would be grateful, even if he didn't know how to thank you.

563
00:24:28,180 --> 00:24:30,820
Roenah's hand trembled slightly on the handle of her mug.

564
00:24:31,140 --> 00:24:33,640
She set the mug down on the marble with doubled care.

565
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,940
The charity event took place on a Thursday.

566
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:40,420
It was an auction in aid of a children's hospital in a vaulted ceiling tall,

567
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:43,980
where the candle arborers seemed too heavy for the wire that held them.

568
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:47,220
Roenah wore a dark green dress borrowed from Marlo's sister,

569
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:49,620
and Jago appeared at her side at the entrance,

570
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:52,460
as if he'd matched the exact time to his own watch.

571
00:24:53,020 --> 00:24:55,340
Odeit Marshaar arrived 20 minutes later.

572
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:58,020
Roenah saw her approach from the other side of the hall,

573
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:02,860
greeting people with thin kisses, a champagne coloured dress moving like liquid.

574
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,980
Odeit stopped in front of Roenah,

575
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:08,300
looked her up and down with a smile too polite to be polite,

576
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:11,680
and said in a tone that carried through the three nearest people,

577
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:16,600
you hold up well dear, a borrowed dress in a hall of this caliper isn't for just anyone.

578
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:18,760
I hope the night is kind to you.

579
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:23,300
The air in the hall became specific, two women near the buffet stopped chewing.

580
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:27,940
Roenah felt the blood rise up her neck and choose between turning into fury

581
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:29,580
and turning into dignity.

582
00:25:30,180 --> 00:25:33,920
Before she could decide, Jago's hand touched the small of her back,

583
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:37,720
firm, without theatrical possession, just presence,

584
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:39,520
and he took half a step forward,

585
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:41,620
shoulder pressed against hers.

586
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:43,220
Odeit, he said,

587
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:45,700
and his voice was no longer lower than usual,

588
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:47,760
only stripped of anything amiable.

589
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:50,700
If you have any doubts about the woman I came with,

590
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,300
put those doubts to me directly.

591
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:55,980
Roenah owes you no explanation about where she buys any dress,

592
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,000
neither do you.

593
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,680
Odeit parted her lips,

594
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:02,120
and something inside her smile gave way for half a second,

595
00:26:02,620 --> 00:26:03,500
before recomposing.

596
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:05,780
How touchy Jago, it was a compliment.

597
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:06,780
It wasn't.

598
00:26:06,780 --> 00:26:09,520
He didn't raise his tone, he didn't need to.

599
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:13,620
Two people nearby rediscovered a sudden fascination with their own shoes.

600
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:14,900
Odeit nodded,

601
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:18,040
murmured a phrase about finding a friend and with Drew.

602
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:21,660
Jago didn't move his hand from Roenah's back for a few more seconds,

603
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,980
and in those seconds she felt everything.

604
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:27,060
His thumb resting exactly on the seam of her dress,

605
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:28,720
the heat of his palm,

606
00:26:29,180 --> 00:26:32,440
the silent weight of being chosen there before an entire room.

607
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:34,760
When he moved his hand away, it was slow.

608
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:36,480
Roenah drew a breath.

609
00:26:36,820 --> 00:26:37,840
You didn't need to.

610
00:26:38,140 --> 00:26:39,800
I did actually, he answered,

611
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:41,360
without looking at her.

612
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:42,980
She knew what she was doing.

613
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:45,220
The rest of the night passed in waves.

614
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:48,040
Roenah won a small lot with the money she had,

615
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:50,220
a pair of glass earrings no one wanted.

616
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:51,820
Jago won nothing.

617
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:53,720
He just watched her from afar,

618
00:26:54,140 --> 00:26:55,100
from across the hall,

619
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:57,180
and every time she raised her eyes,

620
00:26:57,620 --> 00:26:58,560
he was already looking.

621
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:01,020
They returned to the mansion around midnight.

622
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:04,740
She went up to the guest room and stood for a long time in front of the open

623
00:27:04,740 --> 00:27:06,080
suitcase on the floor,

624
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,700
at the bottom of it,

625
00:27:07,820 --> 00:27:09,220
under two folded blouses,

626
00:27:09,740 --> 00:27:11,040
and a pair of old shoes,

627
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:12,280
was the file.

628
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,140
Brown, no label,

629
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:15,880
tied with a rubber band,

630
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:17,760
Roenah pulled it into her lap,

631
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:19,700
sat on the rug and stayed looking.

632
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:21,140
She didn't open it.

633
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:22,940
She ran her thumb along the edge,

634
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:24,300
drew a deep breath,

635
00:27:24,540 --> 00:27:26,700
and returned the file to the bottom of the suitcase.

636
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:30,180
She folded the blouses over it with exaggerated care,

637
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:33,200
as if covering it were enough to undo what labor-neath,

638
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,280
her phone on the nightstand vibrated,

639
00:27:35,900 --> 00:27:37,160
Roenah glanced sideways,

640
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:38,600
a missed call,

641
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:39,580
then another,

642
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:41,480
then a third one she watched arrived,

643
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:45,000
Wallace Vaughn's name blinking on the screen like a silent alarm,

644
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,880
she let it ring until it stopped.

645
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:49,740
She kept looking at the phone until the light went out.

646
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,420
When she lowered her head again,

647
00:27:51,780 --> 00:27:53,880
the phone vibrated a fourth time,

648
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:55,060
a fifth,

649
00:27:55,520 --> 00:27:56,720
Roenah closed her eyes.

650
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,080
Across the corridor,

651
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,700
someone walked slowly,

652
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:01,520
bare feet on the wood.

653
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:03,500
She knew who steps they were,

654
00:28:03,700 --> 00:28:04,940
and she didn't open the door.

655
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:06,480
The phone kept ringing.

656
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:09,620
Wallace Vaughn's fifth call came just after dawn,

657
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:11,920
and this time, Roenah answered.

658
00:28:12,420 --> 00:28:14,220
She was sitting on the floor of the guest room,

659
00:28:14,620 --> 00:28:16,240
still in the wrinkled green dress.

660
00:28:16,620 --> 00:28:18,060
The glass earrings in her lap,

661
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:21,080
the phone trembling in her hand for the sixth time.

662
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:23,560
The rug beneath her smelled of old lavender,

663
00:28:24,220 --> 00:28:26,160
the kind of lavender that isn't perfume.

664
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:27,400
It's time.

665
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:30,100
You vanished, said Hollis, without a greeting.

666
00:28:30,100 --> 00:28:33,840
His voice had that measured calm that preceded fireings.

667
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:35,780
I haven't heard your voice in three weeks.

668
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:37,480
Don't give me behind schedule.

669
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:39,040
It's behind schedule.

670
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,180
That's not the point.

671
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:41,760
The point is the material.

672
00:28:42,260 --> 00:28:42,980
Where is it?

673
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:43,640
I'm working.

674
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:44,720
You're not.

675
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:47,880
Roenah closed her eyes and rested her forehead on her knee.

676
00:28:48,300 --> 00:28:50,500
The knee was cold through the wrinkled fabric.

677
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:53,220
Outside the garden hadn't quite woken up yet.

678
00:28:53,620 --> 00:28:56,080
A shallow grey light spread across the window,

679
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:58,880
as if the day was still convincing itself to arrive.

680
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:01,000
Hollis, Roenah.

681
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:03,100
He drew a deep breath on the other end of the line.

682
00:29:03,620 --> 00:29:04,440
I backed you.

683
00:29:04,760 --> 00:29:05,480
I bought the ticket.

684
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:07,600
Paid for the hotel the first weekend,

685
00:29:07,860 --> 00:29:10,620
kept your shift going with Marlo covering three straight shifts.

686
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:12,040
I'm not a benefactor.

687
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:12,820
I'm an editor.

688
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,840
And an editor needs to deliver.

689
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:18,500
Either you send me something by Monday night or I'll have to make a decision

690
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,520
neither of us once.

691
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,260
She didn't answer right away.

692
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:25,540
Outside, a bird insisted on the same short note near the window.

693
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:28,860
And Roenah caught herself thinking about how Jago used to be

694
00:29:28,860 --> 00:29:31,800
late with the coffee whenever there was a bird nearby.

695
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:33,920
He'd stand out on the porch for a moment,

696
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:36,740
listening, the cup forgotten in his hand.

697
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,660
She shouldn't have noticed that.

698
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:39,720
She had noticed.

699
00:29:40,300 --> 00:29:41,100
I heard you.

700
00:29:41,360 --> 00:29:42,080
She said finally.

701
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,040
You didn't, Hollis answered.

702
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:45,380
But you will.

703
00:29:45,700 --> 00:29:47,760
Monday night, headline or resignation.

704
00:29:48,540 --> 00:29:49,400
He hung up first.

705
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:53,040
Roenah kept looking at the phone for a length of time she couldn't measure.

706
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:56,620
The reflection of her own distorted face on the black screen.

707
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:58,100
She stood up slowly.

708
00:29:58,100 --> 00:30:02,280
She walked to the suitcase which was half open on a wooden chair near the dresser.

709
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:06,420
She pulled the brown file out by the rubber band, sat down again on the rug,

710
00:30:06,860 --> 00:30:08,740
and rested the file on her own thighs.

711
00:30:09,260 --> 00:30:10,760
Her hands were still this time.

712
00:30:11,220 --> 00:30:12,260
Stiller than she expected.

713
00:30:12,900 --> 00:30:14,740
She untied the rubber band slowly.

714
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,520
She opened the first flap.

715
00:30:18,300 --> 00:30:19,580
Clippings of balance sheets.

716
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:22,960
Photocopies Hollis had obtained from some discrete source.

717
00:30:23,320 --> 00:30:27,300
Notes in small handwriting written by herself before she met Jago Quint

718
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:30,560
in a gray, noisy newsroom where the coffee was bad,

719
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:33,200
and ambition still seemed enough to pay the bills.

720
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:38,800
Roenah read two lines of her own field notebook and didn't recognize the woman who had written that.

721
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:39,980
She closed the file.

722
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,900
She tied the rubber band again.

723
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:44,360
She put everything back at the bottom of the suitcase.

724
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:47,700
The partner's dinner was scheduled for that same night.

725
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:52,100
Neve came up in the late afternoon with a dress hanging from a velvet hanger.

726
00:30:52,620 --> 00:30:55,960
Deep wine, straight neckline, sleeves to the elbow.

727
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:58,720
The fabric had a specific weight to the touch,

728
00:30:59,100 --> 00:31:01,200
that weight of something chosen with attention.

729
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:03,460
Roenah looked at her without understanding.

730
00:31:04,060 --> 00:31:08,140
From the master said Neve and set the hanger on the chair against the wall,

731
00:31:08,540 --> 00:31:09,920
he asked me to leave it here.

732
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:12,460
He said the miss isn't obliged to wear it.

733
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:16,280
Roenah laughed without joy, and if I don't wear it.

734
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:21,080
He won't ask why said Neve, with a half smile that didn't quite complete itself.

735
00:31:21,420 --> 00:31:22,180
But he'll notice.

736
00:31:22,620 --> 00:31:23,220
He notices.

737
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:24,800
She wore the dress.

738
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:27,880
She couldn't decide whether it was surrender or courage,

739
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:29,740
and she chose not to decide.

740
00:31:30,260 --> 00:31:32,200
The mansion's dining room had 18 places,

741
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:34,900
and a table that was a vanished skating rink.

742
00:31:35,380 --> 00:31:37,180
There were six partners, three wives,

743
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,400
Silas Ashford at one end in the same gray suit as always,

744
00:31:40,700 --> 00:31:43,600
and the face of someone who has already seen far too much,

745
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:45,380
without being surprised by anything,

746
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:50,380
and you door a quint at the other end, seated as though the seat had been built around her.

747
00:31:50,740 --> 00:31:52,240
Roenah entered beside Jego.

748
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:55,780
She was introduced by him in a sentence that left no gap.

749
00:31:56,300 --> 00:31:58,000
Roenah Pike, she's with me.

750
00:31:58,280 --> 00:31:59,220
It wasn't a description.

751
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:00,580
It was a signature.

752
00:32:01,180 --> 00:32:03,700
The dinner advanced through courses she barely tasted.

753
00:32:04,220 --> 00:32:05,980
There was talk of an acquisition up north,

754
00:32:06,380 --> 00:32:08,140
of a land auction near the river,

755
00:32:08,540 --> 00:32:10,200
of a niece's wedding in Charleston.

756
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:12,960
Roenah answered when addressed and listened,

757
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:14,040
when not addressed.

758
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:16,880
The wine was too good to be wasted on anxiety,

759
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:19,860
so she drank slowly and kept her spine straight.

760
00:32:19,860 --> 00:32:23,180
At some point between the second course and the third,

761
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:26,460
Jego's hand found hers on top of the white table cloth.

762
00:32:26,740 --> 00:32:29,160
He didn't hold it halfway or hide it under the table.

763
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:33,460
He left his hand resting on top of her hand in full view of everyone,

764
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:36,020
and went on talking to the partner to his left,

765
00:32:36,460 --> 00:32:39,140
as if the hand was some object he'd found along the way,

766
00:32:39,340 --> 00:32:40,500
and decided to keep.

767
00:32:40,860 --> 00:32:42,220
Silas noticed first.

768
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:44,960
Roenah saw the small flicker in the lawyer's eyes,

769
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:46,160
almost invisible,

770
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:49,260
followed by a throat clearing that made way for nothing.

771
00:32:49,260 --> 00:32:51,140
You'dora noticed next.

772
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:53,680
The matriarch didn't take her eyes off her plate,

773
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:56,400
but her fork paused half a second in the air,

774
00:32:56,820 --> 00:33:00,660
and resumed moving with a care Roenah had learned to interpret as reading.

775
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,400
You'dora read people.

776
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,160
She did it all the time,

777
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:06,000
without appearing to be doing it.

778
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:08,440
After coffee the partner's rose for cigars,

779
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:10,900
and the wives went off to another parlor.

780
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:12,700
Roenah went up alone.

781
00:33:13,080 --> 00:33:15,280
In the corridor she crossed paths with Silas,

782
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:18,380
who carried a folder under his arm and a look she couldn't decipher,

783
00:33:18,380 --> 00:33:21,500
the kind of look that holds more than one interpretation,

784
00:33:22,180 --> 00:33:23,620
and gives away none.

785
00:33:24,140 --> 00:33:25,580
The night miss, he said.

786
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:27,680
The night miss, Ashford.

787
00:33:28,100 --> 00:33:29,860
He seemed to want to say something more.

788
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:32,260
He weighed the moment, decided against it,

789
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:36,420
and went on down the corridor with the firm stride of someone with a set destination.

790
00:33:37,020 --> 00:33:40,800
In the guest room, Roenah shut the door and leaned against it for a moment.

791
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:44,140
The wood was cold against her back through the fabric of the dress.

792
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:46,320
She thought about tearing up the notes,

793
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:50,140
she thought about calling Hollis and telling him the story didn't exist.

794
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,580
She thought about telling Jago everything that night,

795
00:33:52,940 --> 00:33:55,600
with the wine still in her body and the courage of exhaustion.

796
00:33:56,100 --> 00:33:58,060
She thought about doing none of the three things,

797
00:33:58,580 --> 00:34:00,300
and leaving it all for the train back.

798
00:34:00,700 --> 00:34:04,480
She went to the bathroom, took off her makeup with cold water and cotton,

799
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:08,160
put on a simple linen night gown lay down on top of the bed's bread,

800
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:12,040
and stared at the white-washed ceiling as the house grew quiet,

801
00:34:12,040 --> 00:34:14,180
room by room.

802
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:16,700
She fell asleep without realizing it.

803
00:34:16,860 --> 00:34:18,560
She was woken by the sound of the door.

804
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:19,820
There was no knock.

805
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:23,520
The door opened slowly letting in a thin band of light from the corridor,

806
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:27,580
and Roenah saw against that light, the silhouette of Jago quint.

807
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:29,620
He didn't turn on the room's lamp.

808
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:32,040
He walked to the middle of the room and stopped,

809
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,780
and only then did she notice what was in his hands,

810
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:39,540
the file, brown, no label, no rubber band now.

811
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:42,320
Roenah sat up in the bed in a single motion,

812
00:34:42,860 --> 00:34:46,160
the air left her chest in an exhalation that made no sound.

813
00:34:46,580 --> 00:34:46,760
Help!

814
00:34:47,220 --> 00:34:49,340
Silas, he said, without raising his voice,

815
00:34:49,680 --> 00:34:51,740
he saw a debt prowling this corridor earlier.

816
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:54,220
He thought it best I checked before she did.

817
00:34:54,620 --> 00:34:55,720
His voice was low.

818
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:56,840
It was calm.

819
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:59,720
It was empty of anything she could use to hold onto.

820
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:02,260
Jago looked at the file he was carrying,

821
00:35:02,780 --> 00:35:05,880
leaped through a page she recognized without needing to look closely,

822
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:08,080
and put the page back in its place,

823
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:10,220
with a care that seemed in that moment,

824
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:12,520
the cruelest thing in the world.

825
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:16,040
Balanced sheets, he said, copies of old contracts,

826
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:18,820
a list of names with notes beside them,

827
00:35:19,080 --> 00:35:20,780
her recognized at least three of the names.

828
00:35:21,260 --> 00:35:22,480
He lifted his eyes to her.

829
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:23,860
This isn't an interview.

830
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:25,960
It isn't, Roenah answered,

831
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:28,680
because denying it would have been a worse insult.

832
00:35:29,180 --> 00:35:30,000
He nodded slightly.

833
00:35:30,620 --> 00:35:31,260
That was all.

834
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:34,420
A single precise nod that didn't judge,

835
00:35:34,940 --> 00:35:36,820
and therefore weighed more than any judgment.

836
00:35:36,820 --> 00:35:38,780
You came here for this.

837
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:40,740
I came here for this, she said,

838
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:43,540
and I didn't know I would stop coming here for it.

839
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:44,480
But I did stop.

840
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:45,460
Weeks ago.

841
00:35:45,920 --> 00:35:48,100
I haven't opened that file once since.

842
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,300
Herit doesn't matter, he cut in,

843
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:53,000
and even cutting in he kept his usual low tone.

844
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,600
You opened it yesterday, I heard you open it.

845
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:57,240
I thought you were closing a suitcase.

846
00:35:58,040 --> 00:35:59,620
The silence settled between them,

847
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:02,060
with a specificity, Roenah couldn't fill,

848
00:36:02,380 --> 00:36:03,500
and he didn't try to.

849
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:04,320
Jago.

850
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:06,660
Thank you for coming to Savannah, he said,

851
00:36:06,740 --> 00:36:09,460
and that was the sentence that went through her from side to side.

852
00:36:09,920 --> 00:36:10,940
Thank you for the weeks.

853
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:12,720
The interview is paid for.

854
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,120
If you still want it,

855
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:18,000
I only ask that you leave tomorrow morning before my mother comes down for coffee.

856
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:20,960
She opened her mouth, closed it, opened it again.

857
00:36:21,460 --> 00:36:22,840
Don't do this like this.

858
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:23,860
Like what?

859
00:36:24,380 --> 00:36:26,940
Without yelling at me, he considered the sentence.

860
00:36:27,340 --> 00:36:31,340
He took too long to answer the kind of delay that is an answer in itself.

861
00:36:31,760 --> 00:36:33,820
If I yell, you'll be able to think I'm still angry.

862
00:36:33,820 --> 00:36:36,840
His voice found a note she had never heard in him,

863
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:38,300
too low to have a name.

864
00:36:38,820 --> 00:36:40,060
I don't want you to think that.

865
00:36:40,220 --> 00:36:42,880
I want you to leave knowing exactly what stayed behind.

866
00:36:43,420 --> 00:36:44,520
It was worse than yelling.

867
00:36:45,020 --> 00:36:49,280
It was worse than anything she could have predicted that week or in any week before it.

868
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:51,800
Jago set the file on the dresser near the door,

869
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:54,980
with a precision that seemed calculated to make no noise.

870
00:36:55,460 --> 00:36:56,960
He didn't return it to her hand.

871
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:58,740
He didn't take it with him.

872
00:36:58,900 --> 00:37:01,180
He left it there, in the middle of the way,

873
00:37:01,180 --> 00:37:05,300
like an exposed piece of evidence neither of them needed to examine any more.

874
00:37:05,660 --> 00:37:07,020
Then he turned toward the door.

875
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:07,920
Leave tomorrow.

876
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:13,260
The door closed behind him with the most polite noise a door has ever produced in the entire world.

877
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,260
Rhoina remained sitting on the bed.

878
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,420
Her hands opened on the bed spread.

879
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:20,760
A heart beating in a rhythm she didn't recognise as her own.

880
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:24,680
Outside in the corridor, his footsteps moved away slowly.

881
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:26,840
No hurry, no hesitation.

882
00:37:27,540 --> 00:37:29,960
And at some point between her room and his room,

883
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:32,500
they stopped for a second before continuing.

884
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:33,900
She didn't cry.

885
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:34,940
Not yet.

886
00:37:35,180 --> 00:37:37,560
She kept looking at the file on top of the dresser,

887
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:41,520
like someone staring at an animal that had followed her from too far away

888
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:43,400
to now pretend it was a stranger.

889
00:37:43,920 --> 00:37:46,920
Outside the window, the garden of the quint mansion,

890
00:37:47,620 --> 00:37:52,880
breathed the humid night, the smell of earth and jasmine rising with the breeze off the river.

891
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:56,380
Somewhere near the water, a real owl called out once.

892
00:37:56,860 --> 00:37:59,320
Rhoina thought of the glass owl set with red stone,

893
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:02,420
tucked in a dark velvet box at the bottom of her bag,

894
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:06,780
and felt that this was the memory that would hurt most on the train the next day.

895
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:10,600
The train back left before eight, and Rhoina sat by the window,

896
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,460
because the aisle required looking at people head on,

897
00:38:13,780 --> 00:38:17,740
and people that morning would have seen what she hadn't yet seen in the mirror.

898
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:20,560
She rested her forehead against the cold glass,

899
00:38:20,980 --> 00:38:23,700
and stayed that way for a length of time she couldn't measure.

900
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:29,220
Savannah fell behind in pieces, a roof a tower a line of trees bent by the riverwind,

901
00:38:29,220 --> 00:38:31,820
and none of it hurt with the noise she had expected.

902
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:33,160
It hurt low.

903
00:38:33,660 --> 00:38:37,000
It hurt the way Jago had said, thank you in the small hours,

904
00:38:37,400 --> 00:38:41,620
when she was expecting a shout, anything with enough volume for her to push back against.

905
00:38:42,140 --> 00:38:44,620
The file was still on top of the guest room dresser.

906
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:48,320
She hadn't even asked for it back, leaving it there felt fair.

907
00:38:48,700 --> 00:38:52,140
In the sense that justice is what's left over when everything else surrenders.

908
00:38:52,600 --> 00:38:53,920
She didn't cry on the train.

909
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:56,000
She counted roof panels of cars,

910
00:38:56,000 --> 00:39:01,360
counted poles, counted the times the conductor passed down the aisle dragging a coffee cart.

911
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:04,680
The smell of the machine coffee was cheap, and watery.

912
00:39:05,260 --> 00:39:07,280
Nothing like what Jago had learned to make,

913
00:39:07,540 --> 00:39:10,960
and that idiotic detail was what came closest to breaking her.

914
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:13,480
She reached the grey city just before noon.

915
00:39:13,900 --> 00:39:16,260
The station smelled of lubricant and cheap bread,

916
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:19,480
Rhoina carried her suitcase like someone carrying a witness.

917
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:21,560
She cried in the newsroom bathroom.

918
00:39:21,900 --> 00:39:23,720
It was a dry cry of two minutes,

919
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:28,480
curled up in a stall with her hand over her mouth because Marlo Trent was on the other side of the

920
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:32,620
door, tapping the tip of her shoe and speaking loudly to cover for her.

921
00:39:32,820 --> 00:39:33,820
Come out of their pike.

922
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:38,520
If you stay in there any longer, Holes is going to knock on the door and then I'm going to have to

923
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:39,240
bite him.

924
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:42,300
Rhoina laughed in the middle of the cry without meaning to.

925
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,480
It was an ugly sound but it worked.

926
00:39:44,980 --> 00:39:46,680
She came out with her face washed.

927
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:48,880
Marlo looked at her for a whole second,

928
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,600
without sarcasm for the first time in years.

929
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:54,200
There was something different in her friend's expression.

930
00:39:54,740 --> 00:39:55,660
The shoulders quieter.

931
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:58,640
The way she stood still without her phone in her hand.

932
00:39:59,100 --> 00:39:59,620
You okay?

933
00:40:00,260 --> 00:40:00,600
No.

934
00:40:01,120 --> 00:40:01,760
Rhoina answered.

935
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:03,380
But I will be.

936
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:07,700
Marlo squeezed her shoulder and her hand stayed there too long for a joke.

937
00:40:08,100 --> 00:40:11,640
That was how Rhoina understood her friend had guessed everything before asking.

938
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:14,000
The newsroom had that midday noise.

939
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:16,600
Keys, phones ringing two desks over.

940
00:40:16,980 --> 00:40:21,200
Someone shouting a page number down the hall as if the whole building needed to know.

941
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:26,400
Pallis Vaughan lifted his eyes over his glasses the moment Rhoina passed down the central aisle.

942
00:40:26,820 --> 00:40:27,580
He didn't smile.

943
00:40:28,060 --> 00:40:29,660
He didn't ask how the trip had gone.

944
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:32,740
He simply pointed with his pen to the door of his office.

945
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:34,920
A short, habitual gesture.

946
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:37,040
The kind that allows no negotiation.

947
00:40:37,860 --> 00:40:38,580
She went in.

948
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,260
She shut the door behind her.

949
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:44,640
That office smelled of aged paper and coffee no one had the courage to throw out.

950
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:48,840
And there was a plant in the corner that had been dying for at least two months.

951
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:53,480
It's leaves drooping over the edge of the pot without anyone having noticed.

952
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,240
Pallis sat down his pen.

953
00:40:55,700 --> 00:40:56,520
He said,

954
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:57,780
End of the day.

955
00:40:58,220 --> 00:40:59,540
There's not going to be a headline.

956
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,180
Pallis blinked once.

957
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:02,800
He leaned back in his chair.

958
00:41:03,320 --> 00:41:04,220
Say that again.

959
00:41:04,580 --> 00:41:09,500
There's not going to be a headline Rhoina repeated and her voice came out firm than she expected.

960
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:12,180
I'm not going to deliver what you asked for.

961
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,800
Not today, not next week, not ever.

962
00:41:15,300 --> 00:41:17,040
You went there with a mission pike.

963
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:20,220
I did, and I came back without it.

964
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:22,080
Hollis looked at the desk for a moment.

965
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:25,780
When he raised his eyes, there was less anger than she'd imagined.

966
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:31,080
And more a kind of old disappointment, the kind of disappointment bosses carry from other bosses

967
00:41:31,080 --> 00:41:35,300
before them, piled up over years in rooms exactly like that one.

968
00:41:35,540 --> 00:41:36,600
You know what this means?

969
00:41:37,180 --> 00:41:37,620
I do.

970
00:41:38,180 --> 00:41:40,220
Rhoina set a folded paper on the desk.

971
00:41:40,580 --> 00:41:42,940
I'm handing this over before you have to say it.

972
00:41:43,260 --> 00:41:44,460
Hollis picked up the paper.

973
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:46,000
He didn't open it.

974
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:46,480
Why?

975
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:52,280
He asked, and the question came almost gentle, which frightened her more than an insult would have.

976
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:54,000
Rhoina was silent for a second.

977
00:41:54,380 --> 00:41:56,360
She thought of a pretty professional answer.

978
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:58,460
The kind that looks good in retrospect.

979
00:41:58,900 --> 00:41:59,660
She gave up.

980
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:02,540
Because the story stopped existing, she said.

981
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,120
He stopped being a story.

982
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:07,340
And I don't know how to write about someone who became a person.

983
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:12,260
Hollis looked at her for a long time, with the expression of someone re-reading an equation that

984
00:42:12,260 --> 00:42:15,900
doesn't add up, then he nodded once, almost imperceptibly.

985
00:42:16,420 --> 00:42:18,760
Get out before I change my mind, he said.

986
00:42:19,180 --> 00:42:21,220
And Pike, she stopped at the door.

987
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:22,320
You were good.

988
00:42:22,720 --> 00:42:24,200
Rhoina swallowed before answering.

989
00:42:24,780 --> 00:42:25,480
I still am.

990
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:26,960
Just not for this.

991
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,380
She shut the door carefully.

992
00:42:29,060 --> 00:42:33,420
Hollis was leaning against the corridor wall, waiting with two cups of machine coffee.

993
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:38,260
And she pushed one of the cups into Rhoina's hand without ceremony, like someone handing

994
00:42:38,260 --> 00:42:39,560
over a survival item.

995
00:42:39,960 --> 00:42:40,840
Did you do it?

996
00:42:41,060 --> 00:42:41,520
She asked.

997
00:42:41,520 --> 00:42:42,420
I did.

998
00:42:43,060 --> 00:42:43,360
Shit.

999
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:45,100
Marlo blew on the coffee.

1000
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:47,960
Welcome to the club of the dignified unemployed.

1001
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:49,500
Rhoina laughed.

1002
00:42:49,980 --> 00:42:53,100
It was a short, broken laugh, but it was a laugh.

1003
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:55,520
They went down the stairs instead of the elevator.

1004
00:42:56,100 --> 00:42:59,620
On the sidewalk, the city was grey the way it had always been.

1005
00:43:00,040 --> 00:43:04,380
And Rhoina looked at the buildings without any of the glow that Savannah painted on to even a

1006
00:43:04,380 --> 00:43:05,180
cloudy morning.

1007
00:43:05,660 --> 00:43:07,720
Something was missing from that sky.

1008
00:43:08,180 --> 00:43:10,140
The smell of Magnolia was missing.

1009
00:43:10,140 --> 00:43:14,540
The way the Savannah river appeared between two streets when no one expected it.

1010
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:19,200
A strip of lead-coloured water that somehow made everything lighter was missing.

1011
00:43:19,700 --> 00:43:20,720
E was missing.

1012
00:43:21,260 --> 00:43:23,980
You're going back, Marlo said, without asking.

1013
00:43:24,580 --> 00:43:25,200
I am.

1014
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:26,480
Will he take you back?

1015
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:27,500
I don't know.

1016
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:28,280
He will.

1017
00:43:28,680 --> 00:43:30,640
Marlo insisted looking off into the distance.

1018
00:43:31,260 --> 00:43:35,680
A man who sends for you three weeks in a row doesn't close a door for good.

1019
00:43:36,080 --> 00:43:36,860
He locks it.

1020
00:43:37,160 --> 00:43:37,780
It's different.

1021
00:43:37,780 --> 00:43:42,880
Rhoina looked at her friend, and for an instant, the world stopped spinning so fast.

1022
00:43:43,460 --> 00:43:43,740
Marlo.

1023
00:43:44,300 --> 00:43:44,500
What?

1024
00:43:44,980 --> 00:43:45,600
Thank you.

1025
00:43:45,860 --> 00:43:47,960
Get out of here before I cry, Pike.

1026
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:49,680
It doesn't suit me.

1027
00:43:50,120 --> 00:43:53,980
Rhoina took the night train and slept enough not to look devastated on arrival.

1028
00:43:54,400 --> 00:43:58,940
The car smelled of old fabric and rain, and she kept her face turned to the dark window

1029
00:43:58,940 --> 00:44:03,160
for much of the trip, watching her own reflection without being able to look away.

1030
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:07,920
On Sunday morning, Savannah received the train with the sun coming in from the side,

1031
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:11,000
and the whole station smelled of bakery and river breeze.

1032
00:44:11,520 --> 00:44:13,480
She took a taxi without stopping to think.

1033
00:44:13,900 --> 00:44:15,180
She went in through the front.

1034
00:44:15,660 --> 00:44:16,460
She rang the bell.

1035
00:44:16,900 --> 00:44:17,540
Fielan answered.

1036
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:21,860
His eyes widened for half a second, before returning to normal trained.

1037
00:44:22,420 --> 00:44:24,460
Miss Pike, I need to talk to him.

1038
00:44:24,620 --> 00:44:26,000
He's in his office with guests.

1039
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:27,180
I know.

1040
00:44:27,660 --> 00:44:28,520
Fielan hesitated.

1041
00:44:29,080 --> 00:44:30,120
Then he stepped aside.

1042
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,220
Miss is quint arrived in Aragot.

1043
00:44:32,480 --> 00:44:34,480
He said quietly, almost a warning.

1044
00:44:35,140 --> 00:44:36,760
And Miss Martian came along.

1045
00:44:37,220 --> 00:44:38,080
Rhoina nodded.

1046
00:44:38,380 --> 00:44:41,080
Drew a deep breath once and walked down the marble corridor.

1047
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:44,240
Like someone walking to a trial she herself had scheduled.

1048
00:44:44,860 --> 00:44:47,180
The corridor was silent except for her own footsteps,

1049
00:44:47,740 --> 00:44:51,700
and their echo on the old tiles sounded too firm for the way she was feeling inside.

1050
00:44:52,320 --> 00:44:54,540
J. goes office was in the west wing of the mansion,

1051
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:56,160
and the door was a jar.

1052
00:44:56,160 --> 00:44:59,960
She heard before she saw the voice of Odette Marchant,

1053
00:45:00,580 --> 00:45:04,100
sweet, too loud, that voice of someone who pretends to console

1054
00:45:04,100 --> 00:45:06,140
and measures the effect in a mirror.

1055
00:45:06,800 --> 00:45:08,460
A necessary evil Udora.

1056
00:45:08,960 --> 00:45:12,020
Truly, better to find out now than,

1057
00:45:12,100 --> 00:45:14,100
Rhoina opened the door before Odette finished.

1058
00:45:14,620 --> 00:45:15,960
The entire office went still.

1059
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,920
J. goes stood behind the desk,

1060
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:20,120
dark jacket hands resting on the top.

1061
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:23,240
Udora seated in the green velvet armchair near the window,

1062
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:27,460
back straight as ever, as if her posture were the last line of defense.

1063
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:29,980
Silas leaning against the bookcase.

1064
00:45:30,440 --> 00:45:31,240
Neutral expression.

1065
00:45:31,920 --> 00:45:34,760
Eyes that recognized Rhoina before the rest of his body did.

1066
00:45:35,220 --> 00:45:36,100
Odette on the sofa.

1067
00:45:36,620 --> 00:45:37,440
Glass in hand.

1068
00:45:37,920 --> 00:45:41,540
A smile dressing her mouth until it froze when she saw who had come in.

1069
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:43,000
J. go didn't move.

1070
00:45:43,360 --> 00:45:44,920
Only his jaw tensed once.

1071
00:45:45,480 --> 00:45:45,800
Rhoina.

1072
00:45:46,300 --> 00:45:47,660
Said Silas almost automatically.

1073
00:45:48,240 --> 00:45:49,680
Trying to smooth things over.

1074
00:45:49,680 --> 00:45:53,440
Stay Rhoina asked, without taking her eyes off J. go.

1075
00:45:53,820 --> 00:45:54,440
All of you.

1076
00:45:54,740 --> 00:45:54,980
Stay.

1077
00:45:55,560 --> 00:45:56,680
Odette opened her mouth.

1078
00:45:57,180 --> 00:45:58,540
Rhoina gave her no chance.

1079
00:45:59,060 --> 00:46:01,200
I came to tell the truth, she said.

1080
00:46:01,580 --> 00:46:02,280
All of it.

1081
00:46:02,460 --> 00:46:04,200
I'm not going to apologize first,

1082
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:06,820
because an apology before the truth is an insult.

1083
00:46:07,460 --> 00:46:08,740
Udora raised an eyebrow.

1084
00:46:09,120 --> 00:46:09,860
Nothing more.

1085
00:46:10,360 --> 00:46:11,120
Rhoina breathed.

1086
00:46:11,500 --> 00:46:12,880
Her voice came out firm,

1087
00:46:13,300 --> 00:46:15,740
even though her hands trembled inside her jacket.

1088
00:46:16,220 --> 00:46:18,060
I came to Savannah with two missions.

1089
00:46:18,060 --> 00:46:19,720
The interview was won.

1090
00:46:20,100 --> 00:46:21,880
The other was to come back with material

1091
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:23,500
that would destroy the Quint family.

1092
00:46:24,040 --> 00:46:25,760
My editor wanted a scandal story,

1093
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:28,080
and I accepted because I needed the job.

1094
00:46:28,520 --> 00:46:31,580
I accepted believing I could separate the work from the charade.

1095
00:46:32,060 --> 00:46:32,620
She paused.

1096
00:46:33,140 --> 00:46:33,940
I couldn't.

1097
00:46:34,140 --> 00:46:36,500
Odette let out a low incredulous laugh.

1098
00:46:36,820 --> 00:46:38,020
No one joined her.

1099
00:46:38,200 --> 00:46:40,280
I brought the file, Rhoina continued,

1100
00:46:40,740 --> 00:46:41,840
and her voice didn't waver.

1101
00:46:42,340 --> 00:46:43,860
You already know I brought it.

1102
00:46:44,080 --> 00:46:44,800
It was found.

1103
00:46:45,300 --> 00:46:45,940
It was red.

1104
00:46:45,940 --> 00:46:48,880
And it was returned in the small hours of yesterday morning

1105
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:52,180
with a thank you that hurt more than any shout would have.

1106
00:46:52,520 --> 00:46:53,300
She looked at Jego.

1107
00:46:53,820 --> 00:46:54,480
He didn't look away.

1108
00:46:54,940 --> 00:46:55,760
He didn't confirm.

1109
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:59,780
His face was that of a man counting every word before deciding

1110
00:46:59,780 --> 00:47:01,020
what to do with them.

1111
00:47:01,360 --> 00:47:03,060
I could have gone back to the newsroom,

1112
00:47:03,380 --> 00:47:04,760
written what my editor wanted,

1113
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:06,360
saved my career.

1114
00:47:06,880 --> 00:47:08,420
Her voice rose half a tone.

1115
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:09,860
I didn't write it.

1116
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:11,480
I killed the story this morning.

1117
00:47:11,900 --> 00:47:13,720
I resigned before he could fire me.

1118
00:47:14,060 --> 00:47:15,160
There's no story anymore.

1119
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:16,860
There's no file anymore.

1120
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:20,160
There's nothing left in that guest room that's of use to anyone.

1121
00:47:20,580 --> 00:47:22,380
She took a step forward just one.

1122
00:47:22,700 --> 00:47:24,260
And I didn't come here for forgiveness.

1123
00:47:24,860 --> 00:47:28,580
I came because if I didn't say this in front of everyone who watched the lie happen,

1124
00:47:29,100 --> 00:47:31,000
the truth would remain a private thing,

1125
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:32,320
and the lie was public.

1126
00:47:32,760 --> 00:47:33,760
That's not fair.

1127
00:47:34,260 --> 00:47:35,160
Total silence.

1128
00:47:35,820 --> 00:47:36,960
You'd aura blinked once.

1129
00:47:37,420 --> 00:47:37,680
Slowly.

1130
00:47:38,300 --> 00:47:41,140
Like someone recalculating something she'd thought was settled.

1131
00:47:41,660 --> 00:47:44,260
Odette looked at her glasses if it had betrayed her.

1132
00:47:44,260 --> 00:47:45,480
I dropped the story.

1133
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:46,500
Rowena said,

1134
00:47:46,860 --> 00:47:48,180
and her voice lowered again,

1135
00:47:48,620 --> 00:47:49,420
almost soft.

1136
00:47:49,860 --> 00:47:51,700
Because he stopped being the story.

1137
00:47:52,180 --> 00:47:54,760
I couldn't write about a man who learned my coffee by heart.

1138
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:55,760
She finished.

1139
00:47:56,320 --> 00:47:57,420
Her hands were still trembling.

1140
00:47:57,960 --> 00:47:58,940
She let them tremble.

1141
00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:00,440
Odette rose first.

1142
00:48:00,620 --> 00:48:02,880
Her glass coming down hard on the side tray.

1143
00:48:03,180 --> 00:48:04,100
What a spectacle.

1144
00:48:04,660 --> 00:48:05,280
She said,

1145
00:48:05,560 --> 00:48:06,760
seeking Jago's eyes.

1146
00:48:07,200 --> 00:48:08,760
You're not going to believe this, are you?

1147
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:10,700
Jago didn't answer Odette.

1148
00:48:11,180 --> 00:48:13,060
He looked at Rowena for a length of time,

1149
00:48:13,060 --> 00:48:14,320
no one there could count.

1150
00:48:14,740 --> 00:48:16,660
Then he pulled back his chair, unhurried,

1151
00:48:16,940 --> 00:48:17,700
and stood up.

1152
00:48:17,960 --> 00:48:20,160
Jago crossed the office in a single stride.

1153
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:21,780
It didn't seem like a stride.

1154
00:48:21,980 --> 00:48:23,460
It seemed like decision-walking.

1155
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:25,180
Rowena didn't step back,

1156
00:48:25,340 --> 00:48:27,380
but she held her breath in the middle of her chest,

1157
00:48:27,760 --> 00:48:29,920
as if her body had forgotten how to do it.

1158
00:48:30,120 --> 00:48:31,800
He stopped half a meter from her.

1159
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:33,020
He didn't touch her.

1160
00:48:33,240 --> 00:48:34,520
He just stood there.

1161
00:48:34,820 --> 00:48:36,260
His eyes fixed on her,

1162
00:48:36,440 --> 00:48:39,300
and there was something in that gaze Rowena couldn't name.

1163
00:48:39,580 --> 00:48:41,040
Neither anger nor relief.

1164
00:48:41,040 --> 00:48:43,500
Something that made her hold her own breath.

1165
00:48:43,860 --> 00:48:44,220
Odette,

1166
00:48:44,540 --> 00:48:45,900
he said without looking back,

1167
00:48:46,220 --> 00:48:47,180
get out of my house.

1168
00:48:47,660 --> 00:48:49,180
The silence in the room had weight,

1169
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:52,720
the kind of silence that makes people hold their breath without realizing.

1170
00:48:53,380 --> 00:48:53,740
Jago,

1171
00:48:54,360 --> 00:48:54,720
now,

1172
00:48:55,180 --> 00:48:56,500
his voice came out low,

1173
00:48:56,860 --> 00:48:57,240
courteous,

1174
00:48:57,780 --> 00:48:58,980
the way he spoke to everyone,

1175
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:02,160
and even so, no one in the room had any doubt.

1176
00:49:02,660 --> 00:49:04,620
Odette picked up her bag with rigid movements,

1177
00:49:04,820 --> 00:49:06,040
her fingers gripping the leather.

1178
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:07,620
She didn't look at you, Dora.

1179
00:49:08,080 --> 00:49:09,580
The door slammed behind her,

1180
00:49:09,580 --> 00:49:11,440
with the thin noise of high heels,

1181
00:49:11,760 --> 00:49:12,980
that had lost their audience.

1182
00:49:13,620 --> 00:49:14,840
Jago breathed once.

1183
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:16,300
Then he looked at Rowena,

1184
00:49:16,740 --> 00:49:20,600
as if he were checking a calculation that had taken far too long to add up.

1185
00:49:20,880 --> 00:49:22,840
I want you to hear this, he said,

1186
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:26,180
loud enough for silence and you dora to hear every word,

1187
00:49:26,600 --> 00:49:29,740
and loud enough to carry through the open door and reach the corridor,

1188
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:33,280
where half a dozen of you dora's guests pretended not to listen.

1189
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:35,660
She stays with me.

1190
00:49:35,900 --> 00:49:38,900
And tomorrow, all of Savannah will hear it from my mouth

1191
00:49:38,900 --> 00:49:41,100
before hearing it from anyone else's.

1192
00:49:41,340 --> 00:49:42,360
He paused for an instant,

1193
00:49:42,800 --> 00:49:44,360
as if the sentence carried weight.

1194
00:49:44,840 --> 00:49:46,480
I'm done letting fear choose for me.

1195
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:48,140
He raised his hand slowly.

1196
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:50,740
He touched the tips of his fingers to her chin,

1197
00:49:51,100 --> 00:49:52,640
the touch as light as a question.

1198
00:49:53,320 --> 00:49:55,760
Stay, Rowena felt her eyes sting.

1199
00:49:56,200 --> 00:49:57,060
She didn't look away.

1200
00:49:57,560 --> 00:49:58,080
I'll stay.

1201
00:49:58,620 --> 00:50:00,280
Silas let out the air he'd been holding.

1202
00:50:00,880 --> 00:50:01,960
Udora didn't move,

1203
00:50:02,340 --> 00:50:05,020
but something in the line of her shoulders gave way a millimeter.

1204
00:50:05,480 --> 00:50:08,140
It was the matriarch who broke the silence at last,

1205
00:50:08,140 --> 00:50:11,440
with that voice that never missed its tone even on hard days.

1206
00:50:11,880 --> 00:50:13,100
Out of here, she said,

1207
00:50:13,420 --> 00:50:14,960
addressing neither of them in particular.

1208
00:50:15,540 --> 00:50:16,920
All of you, I need to think,

1209
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:19,080
Rowena and Jago left together.

1210
00:50:19,580 --> 00:50:22,140
Silas closed the door with the care of someone who knows

1211
00:50:22,140 --> 00:50:26,000
that a well-closed door is sometimes worth an entire contract.

1212
00:50:26,500 --> 00:50:28,760
In the corridor, Jago held Rowena's hand.

1213
00:50:29,180 --> 00:50:29,940
That was all.

1214
00:50:30,320 --> 00:50:31,260
He didn't kiss her.

1215
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:32,180
He didn't speak.

1216
00:50:32,620 --> 00:50:34,140
He just held it.

1217
00:50:34,320 --> 00:50:37,400
His fingers laced through hers with a quiet firmness.

1218
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:40,160
Unlike anything she'd known in him until then,

1219
00:50:40,520 --> 00:50:42,180
he let her out onto the back porch,

1220
00:50:42,640 --> 00:50:44,300
the one facing the Savannah River.

1221
00:50:44,820 --> 00:50:47,560
The late afternoon sun fell golden on the water,

1222
00:50:47,940 --> 00:50:49,960
tinting the surface copper and amber,

1223
00:50:50,360 --> 00:50:54,760
and the smell of the garden came heavy with Magnolia wet from the night before.

1224
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:56,720
Somewhere in the middle of the garden,

1225
00:50:57,120 --> 00:50:59,360
an insect sang the same repeated note,

1226
00:51:00,020 --> 00:51:01,240
rhythmic in no hurry.

1227
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:03,880
You killed the story, said Jago,

1228
00:51:04,340 --> 00:51:05,080
looking at the river.

1229
00:51:05,080 --> 00:51:06,560
It wasn't a question.

1230
00:51:07,060 --> 00:51:07,580
I did.

1231
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:09,000
You lost your job.

1232
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:10,020
I did.

1233
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:11,520
He turned his head slowly,

1234
00:51:12,040 --> 00:51:14,880
and his profile against the late afternoon light had a hardness

1235
00:51:14,880 --> 00:51:16,540
Rowena couldn't read in full.

1236
00:51:16,920 --> 00:51:18,700
She could only read the part that mattered.

1237
00:51:19,180 --> 00:51:20,940
I'm going to help you find another one.

1238
00:51:21,140 --> 00:51:21,560
He said,

1239
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:22,640
one you choose.

1240
00:51:23,120 --> 00:51:24,560
Not one I choose for you.

1241
00:51:24,940 --> 00:51:26,000
Rowena laughed softly.

1242
00:51:26,600 --> 00:51:28,760
The laugh came out choked, a little crooked.

1243
00:51:29,220 --> 00:51:31,900
The way laughs happen when the body doesn't quite know yet,

1244
00:51:32,180 --> 00:51:33,860
whether it's crying or smiling.

1245
00:51:33,860 --> 00:51:36,500
You said choose and for you,

1246
00:51:36,840 --> 00:51:38,020
in the same sentence, quint.

1247
00:51:38,520 --> 00:51:38,860
Careful.

1248
00:51:39,440 --> 00:51:40,900
He closed his eyes for a second.

1249
00:51:41,340 --> 00:51:42,400
When he opened them,

1250
00:51:42,560 --> 00:51:44,260
his shoulders had dropped half a finger,

1251
00:51:44,760 --> 00:51:48,460
and his mouth gave way in a near smile Rowena had never seen there.

1252
00:51:48,740 --> 00:51:49,320
I'll learn.

1253
00:51:49,760 --> 00:51:53,220
It was there behind them that the porch door opened.

1254
00:51:53,700 --> 00:51:55,960
Yudora came out without announcing herself.

1255
00:51:56,200 --> 00:51:57,800
She didn't look at Jago first.

1256
00:51:58,060 --> 00:51:59,000
She looked at Rowena,

1257
00:51:59,500 --> 00:52:02,920
and there was in that gaze and a praisele different from the earlier ones,

1258
00:52:02,920 --> 00:52:04,600
without the usual scalpel.

1259
00:52:05,040 --> 00:52:07,040
The matriarch crossed the stone floor,

1260
00:52:07,480 --> 00:52:08,760
and stopped in front of her.

1261
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:11,380
Up close in the low rosy light of that afternoon,

1262
00:52:12,120 --> 00:52:14,180
Yudora seemed smaller than on the night of the ball.

1263
00:52:14,780 --> 00:52:17,020
Smaller and older and less sharp,

1264
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:19,700
as if she'd left her armor hanging on the inside.

1265
00:52:20,260 --> 00:52:22,480
Rowena waited for the blow that didn't come.

1266
00:52:22,940 --> 00:52:24,340
Yudora extended her hand.

1267
00:52:24,740 --> 00:52:26,420
She touched Rowena's arm lightly.

1268
00:52:26,980 --> 00:52:29,220
The thumb sliding once over the sleeve of the jacket.

1269
00:52:29,220 --> 00:52:32,920
A gesture so restrained it could have gone unnoticed, but it didn't.

1270
00:52:33,420 --> 00:52:35,760
Then she turned her head and looked into the hall.

1271
00:52:36,060 --> 00:52:37,160
The wide door was open,

1272
00:52:37,620 --> 00:52:39,480
and from there you could see the empty chair.

1273
00:52:39,880 --> 00:52:42,480
The one that had always been near the window of the main hall,

1274
00:52:42,780 --> 00:52:44,720
its back turned slightly to the side,

1275
00:52:45,020 --> 00:52:47,960
as if someone had just stood up and would come back at any moment.

1276
00:52:48,420 --> 00:52:51,160
Yudora kept looking long enough for the moment to grow heavy.

1277
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:53,360
You have his laugh, she murmured.

1278
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:55,020
Rowena didn't understand.

1279
00:52:55,580 --> 00:52:57,380
She felt her heart skipped a whole beat,

1280
00:52:57,380 --> 00:52:58,880
but she didn't understand.

1281
00:52:59,440 --> 00:53:00,560
Yudora didn't explain.

1282
00:53:00,980 --> 00:53:03,120
She just squeezed her arm once very lightly,

1283
00:53:03,640 --> 00:53:04,660
and went back inside.

1284
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:07,140
The door closed behind her without a sound.

1285
00:53:07,560 --> 00:53:10,140
As if the house were protecting that secret too.

1286
00:53:10,500 --> 00:53:11,680
Rowena looked at Jago.

1287
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:13,220
His jaw was locked.

1288
00:53:13,500 --> 00:53:15,700
His gaze fixed on some point of the river

1289
00:53:15,700 --> 00:53:17,780
that no longer belonged to that afternoon.

1290
00:53:18,460 --> 00:53:18,900
Jago.

1291
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:20,820
Later, he said quietly,

1292
00:53:21,460 --> 00:53:23,200
please, she didn't insist.

1293
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:26,960
She stored the question in the same place where she stored all the details

1294
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:28,660
that didn't yet have a frame.

1295
00:53:29,100 --> 00:53:29,940
She kept storing,

1296
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:32,160
because that was what she knew how to do.

1297
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:36,000
And because not every detail asked to be opened on the same day it appeared.

1298
00:53:36,460 --> 00:53:38,800
Yudora back inside at the end of the afternoon.

1299
00:53:39,420 --> 00:53:41,040
When the river was already dark blue,

1300
00:53:41,500 --> 00:53:44,280
and the mansions lights were beginning to come on one by one,

1301
00:53:44,600 --> 00:53:45,800
as if the house were breathing.

1302
00:53:46,360 --> 00:53:47,100
They ate little.

1303
00:53:47,540 --> 00:53:48,520
No one spoke much.

1304
00:53:49,040 --> 00:53:50,840
Silas passed down the corridor once,

1305
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:54,060
nodded agreeding, and vanished off towards the library.

1306
00:53:54,060 --> 00:53:56,000
Nive brought tea without asking,

1307
00:53:56,480 --> 00:53:58,620
and disappeared before anyone could thank her.

1308
00:53:58,960 --> 00:54:00,980
Then it was Jago who extended his hand.

1309
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:02,180
Rowena accepted.

1310
00:54:02,720 --> 00:54:04,680
They went up the main staircase together.

1311
00:54:05,120 --> 00:54:06,940
Her footsteps echoed on the marble.

1312
00:54:07,440 --> 00:54:09,120
His almost didn't.

1313
00:54:09,440 --> 00:54:12,740
He always stepped as if he didn't want to take up more space than necessary.

1314
00:54:13,300 --> 00:54:14,660
Half way up the stairs he stopped.

1315
00:54:15,120 --> 00:54:16,040
He turned her slowly.

1316
00:54:16,560 --> 00:54:18,580
His hand displayed against the nape of her neck,

1317
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:22,420
and pressed his forehead to hers for a length of time that belonged to no clock.

1318
00:54:22,420 --> 00:54:24,300
I don't know how to do this right.

1319
00:54:24,560 --> 00:54:25,020
He said,

1320
00:54:25,460 --> 00:54:26,920
Too low to be anything but honest.

1321
00:54:27,520 --> 00:54:28,380
No one does.

1322
00:54:28,700 --> 00:54:29,180
He laughed.

1323
00:54:29,660 --> 00:54:31,400
It was a short laugh almost startled.

1324
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:35,040
The kind of laugh that escapes before a person decides to let it out.

1325
00:54:35,500 --> 00:54:36,900
Rowena stored that laugh too.

1326
00:54:37,120 --> 00:54:39,880
She stored it the same way she stored everything that mattered.

1327
00:54:40,240 --> 00:54:42,900
Without noting it down, without recording it.

1328
00:54:43,100 --> 00:54:44,940
Just letting it settle deep.

1329
00:54:45,380 --> 00:54:46,420
They kept going up.

1330
00:54:46,620 --> 00:54:49,640
At the top the corridor had that late night mansions silence

1331
00:54:49,640 --> 00:54:51,620
that isn't the silence of emptiness.

1332
00:54:51,620 --> 00:54:53,540
It's the silence of care.

1333
00:54:54,020 --> 00:54:55,540
The daughter his room was a jar.

1334
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:57,660
He pushed it with the back of his hand.

1335
00:54:58,200 --> 00:55:00,440
A casual gesture that contained a whole decision.

1336
00:55:01,060 --> 00:55:01,920
She went in.

1337
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:03,520
He went in behind her.

1338
00:55:03,700 --> 00:55:04,960
The door closed slowly.

1339
00:55:05,520 --> 00:55:05,940
The kitchen.

1340
00:55:06,480 --> 00:55:07,240
The next morning.

1341
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:09,520
Smelled of coffee and warm bread.

1342
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:12,740
The Savannah light came in from the side through the high window,

1343
00:55:13,240 --> 00:55:14,680
cut into bands by the frames,

1344
00:55:15,220 --> 00:55:17,400
and fell gold and over the white tablecloth,

1345
00:55:17,700 --> 00:55:18,380
over the cups,

1346
00:55:18,380 --> 00:55:21,560
over the still warm loaves that Neve had left in a basket,

1347
00:55:22,080 --> 00:55:24,120
and disappeared before anyone could thank her.

1348
00:55:24,360 --> 00:55:25,860
That was how Neve did things.

1349
00:55:26,380 --> 00:55:28,040
Before hand and without making noise,

1350
00:55:28,720 --> 00:55:30,680
Rowena sat with her legs crossed in the chair,

1351
00:55:31,060 --> 00:55:32,760
the cup warming both her hands.

1352
00:55:33,300 --> 00:55:37,480
Jego sat beside her, so close that his Neve touched hers under the table.

1353
00:55:37,940 --> 00:55:38,660
He didn't speak.

1354
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:42,060
He just extended his hand over the white tablecloth and waited.

1355
00:55:42,640 --> 00:55:44,180
Rowena placed hers on top.

1356
00:55:44,540 --> 00:55:45,480
They stayed that way.

1357
00:55:45,840 --> 00:55:46,400
Unhurried.

1358
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:50,220
While the heat of the coffee rose in a thread of steam between them.

1359
00:55:50,400 --> 00:55:51,280
She looked at the cup.

1360
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:53,620
He had made the coffee the way she liked it.

1361
00:55:53,920 --> 00:55:55,020
Two dashes of sugar,

1362
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:57,400
more milk than any barista would accept.

1363
00:55:57,820 --> 00:55:59,020
He'd made it without asking.

1364
00:55:59,480 --> 00:56:01,800
She smiled into the cup and said nothing,

1365
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:03,500
because she didn't need to.

1366
00:56:03,800 --> 00:56:05,080
From the other side of the kitchen,

1367
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:08,300
through the arch doorway you could see the corner of the main hall.

1368
00:56:08,680 --> 00:56:11,060
And from there you could see the empty chair near the window.

1369
00:56:11,480 --> 00:56:13,880
Its back was still turned slightly to the side,

1370
00:56:14,280 --> 00:56:15,940
as it had been the afternoon before,

1371
00:56:15,940 --> 00:56:19,100
as on every morning Rowena had spent in that house.

1372
00:56:19,640 --> 00:56:21,580
No one had moved the chair during the night.

1373
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:24,220
No one had occupied it as far as she knew.

1374
00:56:24,640 --> 00:56:26,520
On any of the times she'd been there.

1375
00:56:26,840 --> 00:56:29,180
Alaf, someone you'd orah had known.

1376
00:56:29,640 --> 00:56:31,180
Someone Jego had known.

1377
00:56:31,540 --> 00:56:33,860
A name the house had decided to stop saying,

1378
00:56:34,240 --> 00:56:37,520
guarded with such care that even the silence around it had shape.

1379
00:56:38,100 --> 00:56:39,300
Rowena opened her mouth.

1380
00:56:39,860 --> 00:56:40,400
Jego.

1381
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:42,180
He lifted his eyes from the coffee.

1382
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:43,280
He didn't answer.

1383
00:56:43,900 --> 00:56:45,280
Yesterday she said,

1384
00:56:45,280 --> 00:56:48,000
and her voice came out soft, calibrated,

1385
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:49,920
so as not to break that morning.

1386
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:51,520
Your mother said something,

1387
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:55,600
about Alaf, Jego's hand over hers tightened a little.

1388
00:56:56,000 --> 00:56:56,660
That was all.

1389
00:56:57,100 --> 00:57:01,660
A small involuntary squeeze the kind that happens before a person decides to do it.

1390
00:57:01,880 --> 00:57:02,140
Boo!

1391
00:57:02,560 --> 00:57:03,360
She didn't finish.

1392
00:57:03,840 --> 00:57:05,840
Not because he interrupted her with any word.

1393
00:57:06,180 --> 00:57:07,840
It was the silence that did the work.

1394
00:57:08,200 --> 00:57:10,960
A whole round silence that filled the table and the coffee,

1395
00:57:11,460 --> 00:57:13,560
and the savanna light falling between them,

1396
00:57:13,560 --> 00:57:15,540
as if the sun too were waiting.

1397
00:57:16,160 --> 00:57:17,040
He looked at the cup,

1398
00:57:17,440 --> 00:57:18,900
then at her hand under his hand.

1399
00:57:19,300 --> 00:57:23,160
Then for a very brief instant at the empty chair far off golden in the morning.

1400
00:57:23,620 --> 00:57:24,440
He didn't answer.

1401
00:57:24,900 --> 00:57:27,400
Rowena felt then with a cold and new certainty

1402
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:30,720
that there was an entire story living inside that house,

1403
00:57:31,120 --> 00:57:32,960
not in the walls or the old furniture,

1404
00:57:33,520 --> 00:57:36,600
but in the people who lived in it and carried it without saying the name.

1405
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,660
She had just knocked on the right door.

1406
00:57:39,080 --> 00:57:41,160
The door was not going to open that morning.

1407
00:57:41,160 --> 00:57:43,200
She stored the question in her throat.

1408
00:57:43,620 --> 00:57:46,420
The way she had always stored what didn't yet have its time.

1409
00:57:46,820 --> 00:57:48,460
She closed her hand around his.

1410
00:57:48,920 --> 00:57:51,700
Outside a bird sang a high note and flew away.

1411
00:57:52,140 --> 00:57:53,580
The empty chair remained empty.

1412
00:57:54,020 --> 00:57:57,140
Golden in the sun occupying the place it had always occupied.

1413
00:57:57,720 --> 00:58:00,180
And she understood without anyone needing to say it.

1414
00:58:00,540 --> 00:58:03,700
That that morning of peace was only the beginning of something else.
